    <h2>Vision</h2>
    <p>To become the premier partner for venture and private equity firms investing in aerospace and deep tech, transforming technical complexity into strategic advantage.</p><h2>Mission</h2>
<ul>
  <li>To embed engineering-first rigor into investment processes.</li>
  <li>To unlock founder-first deal flow in dual-use and aerospace supply chain markets.</li>
  <li>To elevate fund performance with sharp technical diligence and LP-aligned storytelling.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Positioning</h2>
<p>Cameron William Clark helps venture investors de-risk aerospace bets and win competitive deals by embedding engineering-first rigor, dual-use sourcing strategy, and LP-aligned storytelling into their fund operations.</p>

<h2>Executive Overview</h2>
<p>Cameron William Clark is a trusted advisor to venture capital and private equity firms investing in aerospace and deep tech. A former chief engineer with two decades of satellite and space systems leadership, he now brings engineering-first rigor to capital allocators seeking an edge. Cameron partners with new funds to sharpen investment theses, build sourcing systems around Tier II/III and dual-use startups, lead technical diligence, and elevate capital formation narratives. His advisory model supports fund managers through blueprint design, retained guidance, and incentive-aligned growth into full partner roles.</p>

